'''Raiding''', also known as '''reaving''' or '''pillaging''', is an activity in which several cultures take part. It is an attack on populated areas with the purpose of seizing weaponry, food, gold, or prisoners.

It forms the basis of the economies of the [[Free Folk]]Â [[beyond the Wall]] of [[Westeros]] and the [[Dothraki]] in central and western [[Essos]].

[[Ironborn]] also engage in raiding traditionally, though in their case raiding is also a [[Drowned God|religious]] activity. The [[File:Laiinsport_raid.png|thumb|278px|[[Lannisport]] after being raided by the Greyjoy fleet during the Greyjoy Rebellion.]]ironbornÂ feel that raiding is their right, and have rebelled against the [[Seven Kingdoms]]Â to have the freedom to do so, among other things. This rebellion is known as the [[Greyjoy Rebellion]]. It ultimately ended in [[House Greyjoy|Greyjoy]] defeat, cementing the rule of King [[RobertÂ Baratheon|Robert&amp;nbsp;Baratheon]], and resulting in Lord [[Balon Greyjoy]]'s [[Theon Greyjoy|only surviving son and heir]] becoming a [[ward]] of [[House Stark]] of [[Winterfell]].

In times of war, factions also engage in raiding to deprive the enemy of resources.
